modules.description: This module implements a monadic interface for handling asynchronous computations with error propagation, centered around the `return`, `fail`, and `(>>?)` (bind) operations. It works with the `t` type representing asynchronous values that may fail with an exception. Use this module to sequence Lwt-based operations that require error handling, such as composing asynchronous database queries or network requests where failure must be explicitly handled.

Constructs a cache instance for asynchronous computations, supporting LRU or 2Q eviction policies. It provides functions to retrieve, store, and validate cached values using Lwt deferreds, with key-based access controlled through a user-defined key module. Useful for optimizing repeated I/O-bound lookups such as database queries or API calls.

This module provides Lwt-based asynchronous caching functionality with support for LRU and 2Q eviction policies. It allows storing, retrieving, and validating cached values using deferred I/O operations, handling failures explicitly through a monadic interface. Concrete use cases include optimizing repeated database queries or API calls by reducing redundant I/O through key-based caching with customizable eviction strategies.
